{"lemma":"أَف","slug":"أَف","root":"NTWS","root_slug":"NTWS","root_link":"/words/roots/NTWS","pos":"N","pos_camel":"abbrev","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"أَف","root":"أفف","pos":"N","occurrence_count":3},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["intj","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n911","","n912","n913","n915","n914"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D9%81"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"intj","gloss":"denotes repugnance or annoyance; oof, ugh, faugh","examples":[{"text":"أُفٍّ لَكَ وَلِمَا تَقُولُ!","english":"Ugh! I became fed up with you and what you say."},{"text":"وَقَضَىٰ رَبُّكَ أَلَّا تَعْبُدُوا إِلَّا إِيَّاهُ وَبِالْوَالِدَيْنِ إِحْسَانًا ۚ إِمَّا يَبْلُغَنَّ عِندَكَ الْكِبَرَ أَحَدُهُمَا أَوْ كِلَاهُمَا فَلَا تَقُل لَّهُمَا أُفٍّ وَلَا تَنْهَرْهُمَا وَقُل لَّهُمَا قَوْلًا كَرِيمًا","english":"And your Lord has decreed that you may worship only Him and has decreed kindness to the parents. If either or both ever become aged, do not say to them \"Ugh!\" and do not berate them, but rather speak to them nobly."}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Onomatopoeic."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n911","headword_ar":"اَفَّ","root":"Af","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaw^uf~N","text_ar":"يَوُفٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IDrd, M, Mgh, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yay^if~u","text_ar":"يَيِفُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IDrd, M, K,) the latter agreeable with analogy, (TA,) [but the former, though irregular, is the more common,] inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^af~N","text_ar":"اَفٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, Mgh;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^f~f","text_ar":"افّف","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tA^ofiyfN","text_ar":"تاْفِيفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Mgh, K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tA^f~f","text_ar":"تافّف","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He said"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uf~i","text_ar":"اُفِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.], (IDrd, S, M, Mgh, K,) by reason of anxiety, or disquietude of mind, or by reason of vexation, distress of mind, or disgust: (IDrd, M, K:) held by Sb to be of the same class as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sab~aHa","text_ar":"سَبَّحَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hal~ala","text_ar":"هَلَّلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning “ he said"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suboHaAna A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"سُبْحَانَ ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"” and “ he said"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA A_il`ha A_il~aA A@ll~`hu","text_ar":"لَا اـِلٰهَ اـِلَّا ا@للّٰهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ” (M.) You say also, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^af~afahu","text_ar":"اَفَّفَهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bihi","text_ar":"بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^af~afa","text_ar":"اَفَّفَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bihi","text_ar":"بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taA^af~afa","text_ar":"تَاَفَّفَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He said to him"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uf~i","text_ar":"اُفِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaEala","text_ar":"جَعَلَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino riyHK wajadahaA","text_ar":"مِنْ رِيحٍ وَجَدَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN yataA^af~afu","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ يَتَاَفَّفُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one began to say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uf~i A^uf~i","text_ar":"اُفِّ اُفِّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by reason of a smell which he perceived."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealayohi","text_ar":"عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahu yataA^af~afu","text_ar":"اـِنَّهُ يَتَاَفَّفُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily he is angry with him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"enraged against him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["IDrd","M","Mgh","K","TA","S"]},{"entry_id":"n912","headword_ar":"اَفْ","root":"Af","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^af~i","text_ar":"اَفِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^af~K","text_ar":"اَفٍّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afK","text_ar":"اَفٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uf~N","text_ar":"اُفٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n913","headword_ar":"اـِفْ","root":"Af","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and its vars. (differing only in having the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"f","text_ar":"ف"},{"kind":"text","text":"movent): see the next paragraph."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n915","headword_ar":"اـِفْ","root":"Af","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and its vars. (differing only in having the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"f","text_ar":"ف"},{"kind":"text","text":"movent): see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uf~N","text_ar":"اُفٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A2-  For"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_if~N","text_ar":"اـِفٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_if~aAnN","text_ar":"اـِفَّانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in three places."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n914","headword_ar":"اُفٌّ","root":"Af","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Dirt,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"filth;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uf~apN","text_ar":"اُفَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uf~aA lahu","text_ar":"اُفَّا لَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uf~apF","text_ar":"اُفَّةً","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Dirt,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"filth, to him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"in which the tenween is for the purpose of rendering them indeterminate; (S;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uf~a lahu wa tuf~N","text_ar":"اُفَّ لَهُ وَ تُفٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (T;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"watuf~apF","text_ar":"وَتُفَّةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uf~apF","text_ar":"اُفَّةً","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uf~aA watuf~aA","text_ar":"اُفَّا وَتُفَّا"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (T, S;) the latter of which is an imitative sequent: (S:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uf~N","text_ar":"اُفٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dirt of the ear;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tuf~N","text_ar":"تُفٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dirt of the nails;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, T, M, K; but in the last,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the nail;"},{"kind":"text","text":") the phrases mentioned above being used on the occasion of deeming a thing dirty or filthy, and afterwards on the occasion of experiencing annoyance or disgust at anything; (As, T, M,* TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afafN","text_ar":"اَفَفٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", also, has the former of these two meanings: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uf~N","text_ar":"اُفٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dirt around the nail;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M;) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dirt of the nail;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tuf~N","text_ar":"تُفٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dirt in the nail:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) or the former,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a paring of the nail:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a piece of stick,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a reed, which one takes up from the ground:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) in these various senses they are explained as used in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uf~aA lahu watuf~aA","text_ar":"اُفَّا لَهُ وَتُفَّا"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) or the former signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stink:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Zj, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"paucity;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M, K) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afafN","text_ar":"اَفَفٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M;) or from ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afafN","text_ar":"اَفَفٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing little in quantity;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T; and the same meaning is assigned to this word in the K;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tuf~N","text_ar":"تُفٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is an imitative sequent, (T, M, K,) of the same meaning. (M.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uf~","text_ar":"اُفّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", also, is a word expressive of vexation, distress of mind, or disgust; (M, Mgh;) or of dislike, displeasure, or hatred; (K;) and has six forms; (T, S;) mentioned by Akh; (S;) or ten; (M;) or forty; (K;) or more; (TA;) as follow:"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uf~i","text_ar":"اُفِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uf~a","text_ar":"اُفَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uf~u","text_ar":"اُفُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uf~K","text_ar":"اُفٍّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uf~aA","text_ar":"اُفَّا"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uf~N","text_ar":"اُفٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, M, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uf~i","text_ar":"اُفِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ufa","text_ar":"اُفَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ufu","text_ar":"اُفُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ufK","text_ar":"اُفٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ufFA","text_ar":"اُفًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ufN","text_ar":"اُفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ufo","text_ar":"اُفْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uf~o","text_ar":"اُفّْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uf~aY","text_ar":"اُفَّى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", pronounced with imáleh, (M, K,) i. e. with pure imáleh, and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uf~aY","text_ar":"اُفَّى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"with intermediate imáleh, and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uf~aY","text_ar":"اُفَّى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"without imáleh, the alif [written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"] in these three denoting the fem. gender, and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uf~iY","text_ar":"اُفِّى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", with kesr to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"f","text_ar":"ف"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) i. e., as a prefixed noun with its complement, [the latter being the pronoun of the first pers.,] (TA,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uf~uwoho","text_ar":"اُفُّوْهْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) with damm to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"f","text_ar":"ف"},{"kind":"text","text":", which latter is with teshdeed, and with the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h","text_ar":"ه"},{"kind":"text","text":"quiescent, (TA,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uf~apo","text_ar":"اُفَّةْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in a copy of the M ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uf~apF","text_ar":"اُفَّةً","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ufiho","text_ar":"اُفِهْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uf~uho","text_ar":"اُفُّهْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ifo","text_ar":"اـِفْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_if~o","text_ar":"اـِفّْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ifi","text_ar":"اـِفِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ifK","text_ar":"اـِفٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ifFA","text_ar":"اـِفًا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ifN","text_ar":"اـِفٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_if~K","text_ar":"اـِفٍّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_if~F","text_ar":"اـِفًّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_if~N","text_ar":"اـِفٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_if~u","text_ar":"اـِفُّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", with damm to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"f","text_ar":"ف"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is with teshdeed, [in a copy of the M ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_if~a","text_ar":"اـِفَّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":",] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_if~aA","text_ar":"اـِفَّا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~aA","text_ar":"اـِنَّا"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_if~aY","text_ar":"اـِفَّى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", pronounced with imáleh, and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_if~iY","text_ar":"اـِفِّى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", with kesr, (K,) i. e., prefixed to the pronoun of the first person, (IAmb,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afo","text_ar":"اَفْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^af~i","text_ar":"اَفِّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^af~K","text_ar":"اَفٍّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afK","text_ar":"اَفٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=fi","text_ar":"ا=فِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=f~i","text_ar":"ا=فِّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=fK","text_ar":"ا=فٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=f~K","text_ar":"ا=فٍّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (accord. to different copies of the K,) [all these forms, making the number (forty) mentioned by the author of the K, I have drawn from a comparison of three copies of that work, and I believe them to be correct: some other forms are mentioned by SM as perhaps indicated in the K; but I see no good reason for this: he then adds,] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afaho","text_ar":"اَفَهْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afuwho","text_ar":"اَفُوهْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^af~aho","text_ar":"اَفَّهْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", the last mentioned by IB on the authority of IKtt. (TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uf~i","text_ar":"اُفِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [with its variants,] in its primary sense, denotes one's blowing at a thing that falls upon him, such as dust or ashes; or at the place, to remove therefrom what is annoying; therefore people say, at anything that they deem troublesome, or displeasing, or hateful,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uf~i lahu","text_ar":"اُفِّ لَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as though meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A puff,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"blast of breath, to it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Kt, T:) or [rather] it is a word imitative of a sound; [like"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ugh"},{"kind":"text","text":"in English, both in sound and meaning; and in meaning like our interjections"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"foh"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"faugh;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (Bd on the ex. in the Kur which will be found below, and TA;) denoting vexation, or distress of mind, or disgust; (Bd ubi suprà) or denoting contempt: (TA:) or it is a verbal noun, meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I am vexed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"distressed in mind,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disgusted:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd ubi suprà:) or it is an imperative verbal noun [denoting disgust or abhorrence, like"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"out,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"away"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (IJ, M:) or he who says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uf~aA laka","text_ar":"اُفَّا لَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"uses it in the manner of an imprecation, like as one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wayolFA lilokaAfiriyna","text_ar":"وَيْلًا لِلْكَافِرِينَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and he who says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uf~N laka","text_ar":"اُفٌّ لَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"puts it in the nom. case because of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"l","text_ar":"ل"},{"kind":"text","text":", like as one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wayolN lilokaAfiriyna","text_ar":"وَيْلٌ لِلْكَافِرِينَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and he who says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uf~K laka","text_ar":"اُفٍّ لَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"puts it in the gen. case likening it to words imitative of sounds. (IAmb.) It is said in the Kur [xvii. 24],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"walaA taqulo lahumaA A^uf~i","text_ar":"وَلَا تَقُلْ لَهُمَا اُفِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, TA,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uf~K","text_ar":"اُفٍّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA, [in which other readings also are mentioned,]) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And say not thou to them"},{"kind":"text","text":"(i. e. to thy father and mother)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Ugh,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,] meaning, do not thou deem anything of their affairs burdensome, nor be contracted in bosom thereby, nor be rough, or harsh, or coarse, to them: (Kt, T:) or do not thou say to them anything expressive of the least disgust, when they have become old, but take upon thyself their service;"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uf~i","text_ar":"اُفِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stink."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Zj, T.)"}],"source_refs":["S","TA","M","K","Zj","T","IAmb","Kt","IJ"]}]}}